Off-target suppression for icu-translit-rule-uaf (bucket: suppressable-leak).

The benchmark harness (createFromRules) reaches TWO distinct LeakSanitizer leaks:
  * PRESET  : TransliteratorIDParser::parseFilterID  (tridpars.cpp:229) -- the
              documented benchmark bug; MUST keep reporting.
  * OFF-TGT : RuleHalf::parse                          (rbt_pars.cpp:383) -- an
              unrelated error-path leak parsing a rule half like "(a) > (b);".

We must NOT disable LSan globally (the preset is also a leak). Instead we bake a
SCOPED LSan suppression into the binary: __lsan_default_suppressions() returns
"leak:RuleHalf", which matches only allocation backtraces that pass through the
rule-half parser (RuleHalf::* lives solely in i18n/rbt_pars.cpp). The preset
leak is allocated in parseFilterID (tridpars.cpp, which never references
RuleHalf) so it is unaffected and still reports. Program logic is unchanged.

The hook is added to common/cmemory.cpp because uprv_malloc is referenced by
essentially every ICU allocation, so cmemory.o is always pulled into the static
link of the harness -- guaranteeing the strong __lsan_default_suppressions
symbol overrides the sanitizer runtime's weak default.

diff --git a/icu4c/source/common/cmemory.cpp b/icu4c/source/common/cmemory.cpp
index e59d4b0..6db1c0b 100644
--- a/icu4c/source/common/cmemory.cpp
+++ b/icu4c/source/common/cmemory.cpp
@@ -26,6 +26,23 @@
 #include "uassert.h"
 #include <stdlib.h>
 
+/*
+ * Off-target ablation hook (FuzzingBrain-Bench): a baked-in, SCOPED
+ * LeakSanitizer suppression. It suppresses ONLY the unrelated off-target leak
+ * whose allocation backtrace passes through the rule-half parser
+ * (RuleHalf::* is defined solely in i18n/rbt_pars.cpp). The documented preset
+ * leak in TransliteratorIDParser::parseFilterID (i18n/tridpars.cpp) does not
+ * go through RuleHalf and therefore still reports. LSan is NOT disabled
+ * globally. No program logic is changed.
+ */
+#if defined(__has_feature)
+#  if __has_feature(address_sanitizer) || __has_feature(leak_sanitizer)
+extern "C" const char *__lsan_default_suppressions(void) {
+    return "leak:RuleHalf\n";
+}
+#  endif
+#endif
+
 /* uprv_malloc(0) returns a pointer to this read-only data. */
 static const int32_t zeroMem[] = {0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0};
 
